article.description: — Justin Turner had 25 points as Bowling Green beat Buffalo 76-69 on Friday night.
article.headline: Turner scores 25 to lead Bowling Green over Buffalo 76-69
article.linkText: Turner scores 25 to lead Bowling Green over Buffalo 76-69
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- — Justin Turner had 25 points as Bowling Green beat Buffalo 76-69 on Friday night. Daeqwon Plowden had 13 points for Bowling Green (10-3, 6-1 Mid-American Conference), which earned its sixth consecutive road victory. Caleb Fields added 12 points. Jacob Washington had 10 points. Jeenathan Williams had 17 points for the Bulls (5-4, 3-2). Jayvon Graves added 17 points. Ronaldo Segu had 15 points. The Falcons improve to 2-0 against the Bulls on the season. Bowling Green defeated Buffalo 86-78 on Dec. 6. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
